in # M-79</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_9b5191c2b8fda7f3b54d6781ccf3d30c" level="file"><did><unittitle>Ticket 28 m 820 Class the First for the U.S. Lottery to help finance the American Revolutionary War. Signed by J. Searle.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1776-11-18/1776-11-18">November 18, 1776</unitdate><container id="aspace_c878fa30bde72218057436f38860e419" label="Mixed Materials [31924070783802]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_1905e8f772773ba597dc0854ca3273b0" parent="aspace_c878fa30bde72218057436f38860e419" type="folder">4</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_e29cea9018453d421159b65e9a03f2a0"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Rudin # M-80</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_cb33318285d3cbc5b3091d0d5cf9898e" level="file"><did><unittitle>Wallpaper enlistment</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1813/1813">1813</unitdate><container id="aspace_1b7ba4022b4e2de42829a2e1b1952b70" label="Mixed Materials [31924070783802]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_1cb3c5ccc34b50c361a89ee10ff6ad6f" parent="aspace_1b7ba4022b4e2de42829a2e1b1952b70" type="folder">5</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_dcbdd94cc52676fbfcb76b9e990bab29"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Paper shortages necessitated use of patterned wallpaper for some military documents. Enlistment of John Coffman. Maryland. Rudin # M-99</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_7c51572046de0ba13766d15273a35470" level="file"><did><unittitle>The Star Spangled Banner</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1917-04-02/1917-04-02">April 2, 1917</unitdate><container id="aspace_c9005b874179704487b2932cc39cabbd" label="Mixed Materials [31924070783802]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_257e47e22c86d5741bc0c294f106dc53" parent="aspace_c9005b874179704487b2932cc39cabbd" type="folder">6</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_bebc70b11d0099efbab17c0ed4779d44"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Printed broadside announcing the bill (H.R. 91) proposing that the Star Spangled Banner be declared the National Anthem. Rudin # M-96</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_36da36507bf9fa60b473741185ef4da6" level="file"><did><unittitle>Prohibition prescriptions for alcohol</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1925-04-25/1925-04-25">April 25, 1925</unitdate><unitdate normal="1933-05-07/1933-05-07">May 7, 1933</unitdate><container id="aspace_7c31bcfdfb272ed61c0b064d1b667901" label="Mixed Materials [31924070783802]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_14d2a05aa50cfd0cdfaca2a0fbd875de" parent="aspace_7c31bcfdfb272ed61c0b064d1b667901" type="folder">7</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_647bb0150dedee5a403dfe8d07859f18"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Prohibition prescription for "one pint Rye Whiskey" for James Kelley. Accompanied by a second prescription for Whiskey for James Denby, this being a duplicate to be retained by the druggist. Rudin # M-89</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_8715f4c18a8e856b832d62b506ef462b" level="file"><did><unittitle>Two lottery tickets</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" certainty="approximate" era="ce" normal="1800/1800">1800</unitdate><container id="aspace_8153a892a80c57504bfa14773e85e682" label="Mixed Materials [31924070783802]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_d87651345aad0ad7126d31627813b54b" parent="aspace_8153a892a80c57504bfa14773e85e682" type="folder">8</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_8d32e256ed8599bc35ff4decb3c86f70"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Washington City Canal Lottery for cutting the canal through the city of Washington to the Eastern Branch Harbour. One ticket signed by Notley Young and one signed by Daniel Carroll. Rudin # M-81</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_71a7248edc2bb4b3e03d0a818528fa0d" level="file"><did><unittitle>Three almanacs</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1855/1855">1855</unitdate><unitdate normal="1871/1871">1871</unitdate><unitdate normal="1909/1909">1909</unitdate><container id="aspace_dcbe47805a682102d7d640d4d54d0347" label="Mixed Materials [31924070783802]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_e58ae079ce75bd0b5448c01310ee6dd9" parent="aspace_dcbe47805a682102d7d640d4d54d0347" type="folder">9</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_b8b553ae3aec43871ef091e56d47a733"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Hagerstown, Agricultural Almanac, Hagerstown Rudin # M-105</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_31c64c26e525771cabb40dfe4fe0c947" level="file"><did><unittitle>Confederate envelopes</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" certainty="approximate" era="ce" normal="1860/1869" type="inclusive">1860s</unitdate><container id="aspace_2a0070e58f67c7ccece13bdc7b99a0c3" label="Mixed Materials [31924070783802]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_bd0dfc44527a7706c591dd93202f6879" parent="aspace_2a0070e58f67c7ccece13bdc7b99a0c3" type="folder">10</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_c01a2e327c996fa8b8e20aa6c186744a"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Group of five Confederate hand-made adversity envelopes made from a variety of paper products including bank and legal documents, bill of lading documents, and advertising broadsides. Postally used. Rudin # M-86</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_bb7d03542a95831e8a0a9ec8b8ceed1b" level="file"><did><unittitle>American flag</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1817-01-02/1817-01-02">January 2, 1817</unitdate><container id="aspace_6bb5dc84693f179c5ed8b1e32fc639a8" label="Mixed Materials [31924070783802]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_c3388ba1a2bcdadebd9369a3bf0ff4b0" parent="aspace_6bb5dc84693f179c5ed8b1e32fc639a8" type="folder">11</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_ccade6c776a3d33be2a8dd52213ab407"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>This Congressional Report fixes the ultimate design and evolution of the American Flag as we know it today. Rudin # M-94A</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_7dc092df12a251a044bff04728538086" level="file"><did><unittitle>The Star Spangled Banner</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce">November</unitdate><unitdate normal="1814/1814">1814</unitdate><container id="aspace_45cc18801bbee7c01435065afabe8c49" label="Mixed Materials [31924070783802]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_d47fb3f7a47bfb51fb716c401e21b651" parent="aspace_45cc18801bbee7c01435065afabe8c49" type="folder">12</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_9282f42e753662b417e3f2e5636343cf"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>First magazine printing of the poem that became the National Anthem. (From "The Analectic Magazine" - Nov. 1814). Rudin # M-95</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_7f169fb5204f5ccf031529fb7ddc9629" level="file"><did><unittitle>Oath of Allegiance</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" certainty="approximate" era="ce" normal="1780/1789" type="inclusive">1780s</unitdate><container id="aspace_dc604bf9406536628a4d615b80b5b530" label="Mixed Materials" type="mapcase folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_f80dbf53781a505d7256dc4842e215e7"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Oath of Allegiance to State of New York and renouncing of allegiance to King of Great Britain. Signed by more than 50 local New York patriots. Rudin # M-102</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_6e24f12d4cb17e89170739653d03db34" level="file"><did><unittitle>Descriptive list of 26 deserters from Malone, New York</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce">October</unitdate><unitdate normal="1863/1863">1863</unitdate><container id="aspace_4c2c798a8a97607f922020a6b7e25ceb" label="Mixed Materials" type="mapcase folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_0a90485b3449b288bcb154fd92adbcdf"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Rudin # M-76C</p></scopecontent></c01></dsc>
